summary.purpose: Defines global enums and related type aliases used across the server commons library, including SIM provider identifiers and NX service names.
summary.problem_solved: Centralizes the enumeration of SIM providers and the set of known NX service names, ensuring type safety and consistency across the codebase.

symbols.name: SimProvider
symbols.description_one_line: Enum representing supported SIM card providers.

details.what_it_does: Enumerates the known SIM card providers used by the system: partner, pelephone, celcom, monogoto, and unknown. Each member maps to a lowercase string value matching its key name.

symbols.name: NxServiceName
symbols.description_one_line: String literal union type of all known NX microservice names.

details.what_it_does: Defines a union type of string literals representing all NX platform microservice names: 'bi', 'call_center', 'dashboard', 'devices', 'installer', 'ox_server', 'toolbox', 'end_users', and 'notifications'.

symbols.name: NxServiceNameMap
symbols.description_one_line: Record type mapping each NxServiceName to a string value.

details.what_it_does: Defines a Record type where keys are NxServiceName values and values are strings, used for mapping service names to associated string data (e.g., URLs, labels).
